@NODE "Format" "ARexx For Beginners - Using ARexx For Beginners - Formatting of Text"

@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}AREXX FOR BEGINNERS

USING AREXX FOR BEGINNERS - FORMATTING OF TEXT@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
The text in these articles has been formatted with some text:-

  In @{B}bold@{UB} text

  With @{U}underlined@{UU} text

  @{JCENTER}Centred text
@{JLEFT}

If the above three lines are @{B}NOT@{UB}, respectively, in bold underlined
and centred, then you have an early version of the file amigaguide.library.

Bold and underlining is available from Amigaguide version 39 onwards.

Centring is available from Amigaguide version 40 onwards.

If you have an earlier version, then the formatting will not be as
good as it could be. However, I trust that this will not prevent you
from getting the full benefit of the articles.

If you notice that, in some articles, there is a gap between the line
"=== End of Text ===" and the end of the window then @{B}DO NOT@{UB} go into the
file and delete this space!! It is there because some instances of
@{"cross referencing" LINK "Cross"} can be to some of the last lines of a node. If the
space (blank lines) was not there then the cross reference link would go to
a line before the intended line.


