@ENDNODE

@NODE "Spelling" "ARexx For Beginners - Using ARexx For Beginners - A Note On Spelling"

@{B}@{U}@{JCENTER}AREXX FOR BEGINNERS

USING AREXX FOR BEGINNERS - A NOTE ON SPELLING@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
This note is for all those who use American spelling.

In Australian we use the British conventions for spelling and so these
articles were spell checked using a British dictionary.

So, if this is being read by Americans, you will find things like:-

   analyse    instead of    analyze

   centre     instead of    center

   colour     instead of    color

etc. etc.

After all it @{B}is@{UB} the @{B}ENGLISH@{UB} language ;-)

However, I will not guarantee it is all spelt correctly even in the British
conventions. All typographical mistakes will be blamed on "Bee Bee", our
Blue Burmese kitten who insists on sitting on my lap or walking over the
keyboard while I am typing!

If you find spelling and/or grammatical errors @{" I " LINK "ARB:Misc/Read_Me_First!!/Author"} would appreciate
your advice.


